FBIS4-23980 "drafr119_b_94003" FBIS-AFR-94-119 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 EAST AFRICA Uganda Government To Open Embassies in South Africa, Japan Government To Open Embassies in South Africa, Japan EA1706111094 Kampala Radio Uganda Network in English 1700 GMT 16 Jun 94 EA1706111094 Kampala Radio Uganda Network English BFN [Excerpt] The Ugandan Government has decided to open embassies in South Africa and Japan. This was disclosed today by the minister of finance and economic planning, Mr. Joshua Mayanja-Nkangi, when he was presenting the 1994-95 budget in the National Resistance Council. Mr. Mayanja-Nkangi disclosed that he was the one who announced the ban on trade with South Africa in 1964, when he was minister of commerce, in protest against the country's white minority regime's policy of apartheid. [passage omitted]
